snippet.textDisplay:
What a beautiful concept for introverts like us who can't tell the world what we are going through but deep down we know as zulfii bhai said "sab sambhal jaega". Jaffer's lines just approve that concept telling us from another person's perspective that sometimes we need to hear from not within us but from someone else and that truly feels like a therapy. That someone else knows what I am going through, how tangled I am, in the end we all settle somehow. It can be a fix and it might not be a fix, but it will get better.

Thank you Coke Studio for this gem, when I needed it the most ♥
